The divorce process in Singapore is relatively straightforward, and the court will only grant a divorce if it is satisfied that the marriage has irretrievably broken down. The court will consider the following factors:

Adultery

Unreasonable behaviour

Desertion

Separation for at least 3 years

Separation for at least 4 years

The court will also consider the welfare of any children of the marriage, and will make a decision based on what is in the best interests of the children.
